PN,41202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1774631480
OL,3,CBeavers transform Dorset woodland into
OL,4,Cthriving wetland within a year
OL,6,FThe trust recently added to its wild
OL,7,Frelease beaver numbers with a
OL,8,Fsuccessful reintroduction of several
OL,9,Fanimals on the Holnicote Estate in
OL,10,FExmoor after being granted a further
OL,11,Flicence.
OL,13,FHunted to extinction on mainland
OL,14,FBritain in the 16th century, wild
OL,15,Fbeavers are now poised to play a
OL,16,Fcrucial role in restoring ecosystems.
OL,18,FThe pair have now settled, building a
OL,19,F35-metre dam where the ecological
OL,20,Fimpacts, and benefits, of their
OL,21,Factivity are already becoming clear.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,413,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1774631480
OL,3,CBeavers transform Dorset woodland into
OL,4,Cthriving wetland within a year
OL,6,FThe dam has slowed the flow of a small
OL,7,Fstream, creating a deep and extensive
OL,8,Fpond.
OL,10,FTheir coppicing of trees has opened up
OL,11,Fthe canopy, allowing light to flood in
OL,12,Fand creating an ideal habitat for
OL,13,Fplants, insects, amphibians, birds and
OL,14,Fbats.
OL,16,FThe trail cameras have already picked
OL,17,Fup an otter fishing in the pond, as
OL,18,Fwell as a barn owl hunting there, and
OL,19,Fvolunteers have spotted birds like
OL,20,Fredpoll and water rail.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,413,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1774631480
OL,3,CBeavers transform Dorset woodland into
OL,4,Cthriving wetland within a year
OL,6,FGen Crisford, the National Trust's
OL,7,Fwetlands project officer, said: "The
OL,8,Feffect on the ecosystem in a
OL,9,Frelatively short time is astonishing.
OL,11,F"From dense tangled woodland, the
OL,12,Fbeavers have created a light and airy
OL,13,Fwetland teeming with life above and
OL,14,Fbelow the water.
OL,16,F"We can't wait to see what wildlife
OL,17,Fappears this spring and summer ` from
OL,18,Fdragonflies, diving beetles and
OL,19,Fbutterflies to frogs and newts ` and
OL,20,Fof course, all the animals that feed
OL,21,Foff them.
OL,26,@oD@aOUsD@AOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,413,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1774631480
OL,3,CBeavers transform Dorset woodland into
OL,4,Cthriving wetland within a year
OL,6,F"It's important to remember that the
OL,7,Ftrees the beavers fell don't die `
OL,8,Fthey quickly sprout new shoots. In
OL,9,Ffact, regular coppicing like this is
OL,10,Fessential for keeping the woodland
OL,11,Fhealthy.
OL,13,F"Not only have the beavers breathed
OL,14,Fnew life into the landscape, but there
OL,15,Fare also indications that by slowing
OL,16,Fthe flow of the stream, they are
OL,17,Fhelping prevent the nearby road from
OL,18,Fflooding in heavy rain."
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUzD@XO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
